cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on object recognition from natural images, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new multi-task learning ConvNet architecture, which involves training the network to predict object categories and pose transformations jointly, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of disentangled representations and the focus on retaining other factors of variation also suggest relevance to neural networks (cs.NE) and robotics (cs.RO).
